<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4889158>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 14. Pupa of Thiotricha lumnitzeriella sp. nov. A, Head and thorax, dorsal view.Arrow indicates many minute granular projections on vertex; B, Abdomen, ventral view.Arrow indicates an oval pad equipped with a row of spines and A10 with triangular projections; C, A7, dorsal view.Arrow indicates a transverse row of tergal spinules on both anterior and caudal margins; D, A7, lateral view. Arrow indicates an oval pad equipped with a row of spines and rows of tergal spinules. Scale bar: 0.40 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4889158/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4889142>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. Thiotricha lumnitzeriella sp. nov. and its host plant. A, Habitat; B, Larval portable case attached to the underside of a leaf; C, Host plant: Lumnitzera racemosa (Combretaceae); D, Leaf tissues consumed by the larvae; E, Flower bud with hole made by the larva; F, Protruding larva from the case; G, Larva carrying the portable case; H, Case enclosed with silk; I, Larva; J, Pupa; K, Pupal exuviae left by an emerged adult; L, Resting adult." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4889142/files/figure.png" .

